    email: mahale.ajay01@gmail.com
abstract: >
  Glassbox 2.9 is a free, open-source mechanistic interpretability and EU AI Act
  compliance audit toolkit for transformer language models, built on TransformerLens.
  It implements attribution patching in O(3) forward passes,
  auto-discovers minimum faithful circuits (MFC),
  computes bootstrap 95% confidence intervals on faithfulness metrics,
  measures cross-model circuit alignment via the Functional Circuit Alignment Score (FCAS),
  projects the residual stream via a logit lens,
  scores directed computation-graph edges via Edge Attribution Patching (EAP),
  decomposes circuit components into SAE features via sae-lens,
  computes Q/K/V head-composition scores (Elhage et al. 2021),
  maps token-level gradient-times-embedding saliency,
  provides a tamper-evident SHA-256 hash-chained audit log,
  a GitHub Actions composite action for CI/CD compliance gating,
  a zero-dependency TypeScript SDK (Node/Deno/Bun/browser),
  and Jupyter notebook widgets for interactive circuit visualization.
keywords:
  - mechanistic-interpretability
  - attribution-patching
  - sparse-autoencoder
  - head-composition
  - transformer-circuits
  - explainability
  - deep-learning
  - TransformerLens
  - GPT-2
  - circuit-discovery
